## Code Conventions

- Prefer small, typed modules with explicit exported APIs
- Avoid `any`; narrow unknowns with type guards
- Keep functions pure when possible; isolate IO
- Prefer `const`, early returns, and clear naming

## Next.js / React Conventions

- App Router: keep route files in `app/**/page.tsx`, `app/**/layout.tsx`
- Keep `app/**/page.tsx` thin and server-first:
  - parse and validate params (use parse helpers + `notFound()`)
  - delegate browser/storage/UI state to `components/screens/**` and `lib/hooks/**`
- `"use client"` only when necessary; keep client components minimal
- Avoid introducing new global providers

## UI / Tailwind Conventions

- Reuse existing design tokens: `app/globals.css` and `tailwind.config.ts`
- Prefer composing shared UI primitives:
  - `Surface` — `.surface` containers (supports `variant`)
  - `Button`, `ButtonLink` — `.touch-button` + variants
  - `Chip` — pill badges
  - `HeroHeader` — repeated hero sections
  - `CenteredPanel` — centered locked/not-found/loading panels
- Visible focus styles (`:focus-visible` patterns)
- Touch-friendly targets (~44–52px)
- RTL default: keep `dir="rtl"`; use `dir="ltr"` only for math inputs/expressions

## `data-testid` in UI Components

- Every custom component that renders a DOM root must accept and **forward** `data-testid`
- Use `testIds.screen.*` for Tier-1 anchors and `childTid()` for nested elements (see `testids.mdc`)
- No Hebrew/localized text in test IDs
- Run `npm run check:testids` before concluding

## Analytics / Telemetry

- Use existing analytics module (`lib/analytics/events.ts`) only
- Do not invent new storage keys or event pipelines
- Add new event names only when there is clear product value; keep payloads small and typed
- Never log sensitive data

## Data + Progress Storage

- **Backward compatibility is a user-visible requirement** (not only “schema version”): see **`AGENTS.md` → Data & Storage Rules** for principle, content-ID stability, anti-patterns, and tests when migrations change.
- Treat persisted schemas as versioned: prefer additive changes
- Breaking changes require version bump + migration + MAX mode
- Key format: `kids_math.<domain>.v<schema>.grade.${grade}`
- Sanitize loaded payloads, fail-safe to defaults on parse errors
- **Editing any `lib/*/storage.ts` file → auto-escalate to MAX**

## Routing Helpers

- Use route builders from `lib/routes.ts` — never hardcode path strings
- Preserve query state (e.g. preview flags) through helper utilities

## Hydration and Browser-only State

- Guard reads of `window`, URL query, cookies, localStorage until hydrated
- Keep browser-only IO in client components/hooks with stable fallback UI until ready

## Security Checklist (before every handoff)

```
SECURITY GATE
=============
[ ] No hardcoded secrets (grep: API_KEY, SECRET, TOKEN, PASSWORD, sk-, pk_)
[ ] No console.log in production code (non-test .ts/.tsx)
[ ] No sensitive data in data-testid values
[ ] No unvalidated user input reaching storage or DOM
[ ] Cookie operations use proper flags (httpOnly, secure, sameSite)
[ ] API route handlers validate inputs
[ ] No TODO/FIXME/HACK in security-critical code paths

Result: [PASS / FAIL — list findings with severity]
```

**If CRITICAL finding** → auto-BLOCK, stop work, fix immediately.
**If HIGH finding** → BLOCK merge, must fix before proceeding.

